-----Explaination-----

Create restore point
Get Restore Point
Run Restore Point

-----Example-----

#Create a Restore point, update 'restore' to unique name
Enable-ComputerRestore -Drive C:
vssadmin resize shadowstorage /for=c: /on=c: /maxsize=5%
Checkpoint-Computer -Description "restore" -RestorePointType MODIFY_SETTINGS

#Retrieve existing Restore points
Get-ComputerrestorePoint

#Initiate Restore Point Process
Restore-Computer -Restorepoint <name>

#You can also combine the latter two commands into a single statement
Get-ComputerrestorePoint <name> | Restore-Computer

-----Notes-----

Different 'RestorePointType'
-Application_Install
-Application_Uninstall
-Device_Driver_Install
-Modify_Settings
**The default setting, if none specified, is Application_Install

Use switches for Get-ComputerRestorePoints i.e. '-RestorePoint <name>'


-----End-----
